175C 101st Legislative Session 175
2026 South Dakota Legislature
Senate Bill 175
AMENDME NT 175C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Senator Carley
1 An Act to require that an individual provide proof of citizenship when registering to
2 vote using the voter registration form prescribed by the State Board of
3 Elections and to declare an emergency.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
5 Section 1. That § 12-4-1 be AMENDED:
6 12-4-1. An individual who is a resident of this state, as defined in § 12-1-4, and
7 has or will have the qualifications of a voter prescribed by § 12-3-1 or 12-3-1.1 at the
8 next ensuing municipal, primary, general, or school district election, is entitled to be
9 registered as a voter in the election precinct in which the person maintains residenceAn
10 individual is entitled to register as a voter of this state if the individual:
11 (1) Is a citizen of the United States and has provided sufficient evidence, as set forth
12 in section 2 of this Act, to demonstrate the individual's citizenship;
13 (2) Is a resident, as defined in § 12-1-4, of the precinct in which the individual is
14 registering as a voter;
15 (3) On or before the next election, is at least eighteen years of age; and
16 (4) Is not otherwise disqualified from voting.
17 An individual eligible to vote may vote only in the election precinct where the
18 person maintains residence the individual is a resident.
19 An individual who is a resident of a place that is within the boundaries of this state,
20 which has been ceded to or acquired by the federal government, may not be denied the
21 right to vote in any election held in the precinct where the individual is a resident if the
22 individual is otherwise qualified to vote in the election.
23 Section 2. That § 12-4-1.3 be AMENDED:
24 12-4-1.3. If an individual applies to register as a voter of this state or to vote by
25 absentee ballot, using only the address of a commercial mail receiving agency, mail
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

175C 2 175
1 forwarding service, or other post office box as the individual's residence address, without
2 providing a description of the location of the individual's habitation, the individual does
3 not meet the requirements to be a resident of this state for the purposes of this title, and
4 may be registered only as a federal voter. If an individual who does not meet the
5 requirements to be a resident of this state is eligible to vote pursuant to this section, the
6 county auditor must indicate that the individual is eligible to vote only as a federal voter.A
7 county auditor must designate an individual as a federal voter if:
8 (1) At the time the individual applies to register as a voter or to vote by absentee
9 ballot, the individual provides only the address of a commercial mail receiving
10 agency, mail forwarding service, or other post office box as the address where the
11 individual is a resident, without providing a description of the location of the
12 individual's habitation; or
13 (2) The individual applies to register as a voter and does not provide any
14 documentation demonstrating that the individual is a United States citizen,
15 provided that the individual is not already registered as a voter of another county
16 of this state.
17 The county auditor shall prepare a ballot that lists only the names of the candidates
18 for United States senator, United States representative, and president and vice president
19 of the United States, as certified by the secretary of state pursuant to § 12-8-8, and the
20 names of the presidential electors designated for each candidate. The county auditor or
21 member of the precinct election board shall provide the ballot to any individual who has
22 been designated as a federal voter, by the county auditor.
23 For the purposes of this section, "federal voter" means an individual who is eligible
24 to vote in elections for presidential electors, United States senator, or United States
25 representative at a primary, runoff, special, or general election.
26 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 12-4:
27 Any individual applying to register as a voter shall provide documentation, along
28 with the application, to demonstrate that the individual is a United States citizen. The
29 individual shall present:
30 (1) The individual's South Dakota driver license or nondriver identification card,
31 provided that the license or identification card was issued after July 1, 2025, and
32 indicates that the individual has provided sufficient documentation to demonstrate
33 that the individual is a United States citizen;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

175C 3 175
1 (2) A valid driver license or nondriver identification card issued by any other state or
2 territory of the United States, provided that the license or identification card
3 indicates that the individual has provided sufficient documentation to demonstrate
4 that the individual is a United States citizen;
5 (3) The individual's tribal identification card; or
6 (4) A legible photocopy of:
7 (a) The individual's birth certificate;
8 (b) The pages of the individual's United States passport, which identify the
9 applicant and show the individual's passport number; or
10 (c) A consular report of birth abroad issued by the United States Department
11 of State for the individual;
12 (d) The individual's certificate of naturalization; or
13 (e) Any other type of acceptable documentary evidence of citizenship permitted
14 under 42 C.F.R. § 436.407 (January 1, 2026).
15 If an individual provides a copy of the individual's certificate of naturalization, the
16 county auditor must verify the number of the certificate of naturalization with the United
17 States Immigration and Naturalization Service.
18 Section 4. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 12-4:
19 Except as otherwise provided by this section, any individual is deemed to have
20 provided satisfactory documentation demonstrating the individual's citizenship and is not
21 required to resubmit documentation demonstrating the individual's citizenship if the
22 individual is registered as a voter on or before July 1, 2026.
23 If an individual who is registered as a voter of this state registers as a voter of
24 another county within this state, the individual must provide documentation
25 demonstrating the individual's citizenship.
26 Section 4. That § 34-10-7 be AMENDED:
27 34-10-7. Any person qualified as an elector under § 12-3-1 and resident of the
28 proposed hospital district shall be entitled to vote.An individual is entitled to vote at an
29 election conducted in a proposed hospital district if the individual is registered as a voter,
30 pursuant to chapter 12-4, and is a resident of the proposed hospital district.
31 Section 5. That § 12-3-1 be REPEALED.
