175C 4 175
1 An individual may vote at an election in this state only if, at the time of the election,
2 the individual:
3 (1) Is a citizen of the United States;
4 (2) Maintains residence in this state, as defined in § 12-1-4;
5 (3) Is at least eighteen years of age;
6 (4) Is not otherwise disqualified; and
7 (5) Complies with the law regarding the registration of voters, pursuant to chapter 12-
8 4.
9 Section 6. That § 12-3-1.1 be REPEALED.
10 No person residing on an area within the boundaries of this state which has been
11 ceded to, or acquired by, the federal government shall be denied the right to vote in
12 elections of this state or of the county, municipality, school district, or special district
13 wherein such area lies if such person is otherwise qualified to vote in such election or
14 elections.
15 Section 7. Whereas, this Act is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public peace,
16 health, or safety, an emergency is hereby declared to exist, and this Act shall be in full force
17 and effect from and after its passage and approval.
